text: Pervomaysky () is a rural locality (a village) in Shemyaksky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 307 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 54 km from Ufa, 4 km from Oktyabrsky. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Pervomaysky, Ufimsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
